    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The repair or re-equipping of an object. In an archaeological context this refers to identifying flakes and other pieces of broken objects or chipped stones and, if possible, reassembling them on a lithic core in order to learn more about the process of making stone tools.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
